The paper proposes a new clustering method for single cell transcriptomic data that addresses challenges in clustering quality, prior knowledge on number of clusters, and computational speed. The method is based on Parallel Split Merge Sampling on Dirichlet Process Mixture Model, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of high performance computing (HPC) clusters, which relates to the categories of databases (cs.DB) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
